{
  "texts": [
    "This procedure predicts a |V|-dimension probability distribution p |V| for the tokens in the vocabulary V (line 4).",
    "Subsequently, the token tok with the highest probability is selected using the commonly used ARGMAX function [37] (line 5).",
    "The selected token tok is then appended to F (line 6).",
    "If tok corresponds to the <EOS> token, the iterative process concludes, yielding the final generated function (lines 7-8).If tok corresponds to the special token <COMP>, the autocompletion tool is triggered to provide a list of completion suggestions denoted as C. These suggestions are produced based on the code repository R and the caret position P ′ after inserting F at P (lines 9-11).",
    "Notably, when F is inserted using the INSERT procedure, any <COMP> tokens within it are removed to prevent syntax errors."
  ]
}